# Architecture and Best Practices
- Follow WebExtension framework for Thunderbird add-ons. 
- Divide responsibilities between background, content scripts, and UI pages. 
- Configure permissions following the principle of least privilege. 
- Use modern build tools if necessary. 
- Implement proper version control and change management.

# Thunderbird API Usage
- Use messenger.* APIs correctly (messages, addressbooks, etc.). 
- Handle asynchronous operations with Promises. 
- Understand and use Thunderbird-specific features and APIs. 
- Refer to official API documentation: [https://webextension-API.thunderbird.net/en/stable/]

# Follow Official Documentation
- Refer to official Thunderbird add-on documentation: [https://developer.thunderbird.net/add-ons/] 
- Stay updated with changes and new features. 
- Follow best practices and guidelines provided by Mozilla.

# Publishing and Maintenance
- Prepare the add-on for the official Thunderbird add-on repository. 
- Write clear documentation and privacy policies. 
- Implement update mechanisms. 
- Handle user feedback. 
- Maintain the add-on over time.









